approvedImplementationCallers(address).details: Returns the list of callers approved to delegate call into `implementation`.

approvedImplementations().details: Returns the list of approved implementations.

approvedSignatureCheckers(bytes32).details: Returns the list of approved signature checkers for `keyHash`.

canExecute(bytes32,address,bytes).details: Returns whether a key hash can execute a call.

computeDigest((address,uint256,bytes)[],.details: Computes the EIP712 digest for `calls`. If the the nonce starts with `MULTICHAIN_NONCE_PREFIX`, the digest will be computed without the chain ID. Otherwise, the digest will be computed with the chain ID.

execute(bytes32,bytes).details: Override to allow for a delegate call workflow. Any implementation contract used in the delegate call workflow must be approved first.

getKey(bytes32).details: Returns the key corresponding to the `keyHash`. Reverts if the key does not exist.

getNonce(uint192).details: Return current nonce with sequence key.

hash((uint40,uint8,bool,bytes)).details: Returns the hash of the key, which does not includes the expiry.

invalidateNonce(uint256).details: Increments the sequence for the `seqKey` in nonce (i.e. upper 192 bits). This invalidates the nonces for the `seqKey`, up to `uint64(nonce)`.

isValidSignature(bytes32,bytes).details: Checks if a signature is valid. Note: For security reasons, we can only let this function validate against the original EOA key and other super admin keys. Otherwise, any session key can be used to approve infinite allowances via Permit2 by default, which will allow apps infinite power.

keyAt(uint256).details: Returns the authorized key at index `i`.

keyCount().details: Returns the number of authorized keys.

removeSpendLimit(bytes32,address,uint8).details: Removes the daily spend limit of `token` for `keyHash` for `period`.

setCanExecute(bytes32,address,bytes4,boo.details: Sets the ability of a key hash to execute a call with a function selector.

setImplementationApproval(address,bool).details: Sets whether `implementation` is approved to be delegate called into.

setImplementationCallerApproval(address,.details: Sets whether `implementation` can be delegate called by `caller`.

setSignatureCheckerApproval(bytes32,addr.details: Sets whether `checker` can use `isValidSignature` to successfully validate a signature for a given key hash.

setSpendLimit(bytes32,address,uint8,uint.details: Sets the daily spend limit of `token` for `keyHash` for `period`.

spendInfos(bytes32).details: Returns an array containing information on all the daily spends for `keyHash`.

startOfSpendPeriod(uint256,uint8).details: Rounds the unix timestamp down to the period.

supportsExecutionMode(bytes32).details: Supported modes: - `0x01000000000000000000...`: Single batch. Does not support optional `opData`. - `0x01000000000078210001...`: Single batch. Supports optional `opData`. - `0x01000000000078210002...`: Batch of batches. - `0xff000000000000000000...`: Delegate call.

unwrapAndValidateSignature(bytes32,bytes.details: Returns if the signature is valid, along with its `keyHash`. The `signature` is a wrapped signature, given by `abi.encodePacked(bytes(innerSignature), bytes32(keyHash), bool(prehash))`.

upgradeProxyDelegation(address).details: Upgrades the proxy delegation. If this delegation is delegated directly without usage of EIP7702Proxy, this operation will not affect the logic until the authority is redelegated to a proper EIP7702Proxy. The `newImplementation` should implement `upgradeProxyDelegation` or similar, otherwise upgrades will be locked and only a new EIP-7702 transaction can change the authority's logic.
